        "content": "<p>I'd like to use the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disjoint_union\">disjoint union</a> of smooth manifolds, but perhaps let's start with topological spaces: does mathlib have this already? Searching the docs or moogle yields lots of results about unions of disjoint sets... which is not really what I'm interested in.</p>\n<p>Results like <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Profinite.instPreservesFiniteCoproductsTopCatToTopCat#doc\">docs#Profinite.instPreservesFiniteCoproductsTopCatToTopCat</a> seem to imply mathlib has things in this direction, but I cannot find \"TopCat has finite coproducts\" or similar either. Does mathlib really not have this, or where should I look instead?</p>",
        "id": 451614947,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Rothgang",
        "timestamp": 1721073133
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>TopCat</code> (should) have all coproducts (and even all colimits)</p>",
        "id": 451622684,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1721074684
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/863d11f8bd84235a37dda2f8247db2106024876b/Mathlib/Topology/Category/TopCat/Limits/Basic.lean#L185\">https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/863d11f8bd84235a37dda2f8247db2106024876b/Mathlib/Topology/Category/TopCat/Limits/Basic.lean#L185</a></p>",
        "id": 451622853,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1721074742
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the definition of the colimit cocone is here: <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/863d11f8bd84235a37dda2f8247db2106024876b/Mathlib/Topology/Category/TopCat/Limits/Basic.lean#L140\">https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/863d11f8bd84235a37dda2f8247db2106024876b/Mathlib/Topology/Category/TopCat/Limits/Basic.lean#L140</a></p>",
        "id": 451622922,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1721074764
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>note that it uses the supremum of the coinduced topologies. So if you don't want to use category theory, you can just use the api for supremums of topologies and the api for coinduced topologies.</p>",
        "id": 451623095,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1721074806
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In other words: all the ingredients are there, and a PR adding this consequence would be welcome?</p>",
        "id": 451627220,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Rothgang",
        "timestamp": 1721076299
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>what are you looking for precisely?</p>",
        "id": 451627260,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1721076313
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's not clear to me that anything really needs to be added.</p>",
        "id": 451627286,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1721076323
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Isn't this <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=instTopologicalSpaceSum#doc\">docs#instTopologicalSpaceSum</a> ?</p>",
        "id": 451664496,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1721095306
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That’s the topology, but I’m not sure whether Michael is looking for more (e.g. the universal property)</p>",
        "id": 451670196,
