    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"690858\">Daniel Weber</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Disjoint.20union.20of.20topological.20spaces/near/451664496\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Isn't this <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=instTopologicalSpaceSum#doc\">docs#instTopologicalSpaceSum</a> ?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>That's what I was looking for, thanks! (I wanted to be able to write \"disjoint union\" without having to say three lines of category theory - it's great to see this is possible!)</p>",
        "id": 451765896,
